		 Subject: Meeting Notes

This note summarizes the discussion and decisions made in today's meeting.  
If your take on the meeting is different or if I have not accurately outlined 
the decisions, please let me know and I will correct the synopsis below.

1. Facilities room and work phone for Houston Headquarters personnel will be 
published in PeopleFinder and instructions will be provided on how to contact 
facilities to correct data if needed.  The verbage for these instructions 
will be developed with input from facilities.
2. The room and work phone in eHROnline will be display only for Houston 
Headquarters personnel and will show the room and phone on Infotype 1028 in 
SAP.  Instructions will be provided on how to contact facilities to correct 
data if needed.  Whether or not to make these fields display only in 
eHROnline can be determined by use of the SAP "z" table of Houston 
Headquarters personnel areas currently used in the paycheck distribution 
process.
3. SAP HR Houston will continue to process a nightly interface from 
facilities to update room and work number on Infotype 1028.  This interface 
can use either SS# or SAP ID.  The ISC will work with facilities to change 
the interface to use Apeture data when FMS is retired.
4. "Global Data" people located in Houston Headquarters who are entered into 
SAP in the new personnel area "Global Data" will have facilities data sent to 
PeopleFinder.  These folks will be able to provide facilities with an SAP ID 
instead of a SS# for entry into the facilities churn database.  
5.  Contractors and "Global Data" people who are not in SAP HR Houston will 
still be able to enter room and work phone in eHROnline.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
